'''Owen Thor Walker''' (online pseudonym '''AKILL''') is a [[Hacker (computer security)|computer hacker]] living in [[New Zealand]], who was discharged without conviction despite pleading guilty to several charges of 'cybercrime'.<ref name="nzherald-convicted">{{Cite news|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/section/1/story.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=10521796 |title=Superhacker convicted of international cyber crime |publisher=[[New Zealand Herald]] | date=16 July 2008}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/7509052.stm|title=NZ teenage hacker charges dropped|date=16 July 2008 |publisher=BBC News|accessdate=2009-01-17}}</ref> In 2008 he admitted to being the ringleader of an international hacking organization estimated to have caused $26 million worth of damage.<ref name="nzherald-convicted" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/index.cfm?objectid=10484625|title=Internet pushes boundaries in 2007|publisher=New Zealand Herald | date=29 December 2007}}</ref>
==History== Walker was home-schooled from the age of 13.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/section/1/story.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=10479450 |title=Named: NZ teen in cyber-scam |publisher=New Zealand Herald | date=1 December 2007}}</ref><ref name="nzherald-selftaught">{{Cite news| url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/section/1/story.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=10501425 |title=Self-taught hacker admits worldwide attacks |publisher=New Zealand Herald | date=1 April 2008}}</ref> He received no formal computer training, instead teaching himself programming and encryption.<ref name="nzherald-convicted" /><ref name="nzherald-selftaught" /><ref>{{Cite news| url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/section/1/story.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=10522449|title=The cyber star left to shine|publisher=New Zealand Herald|accessdate=2008-07-22|date=20 July 2008}}</ref> He had been diagnosed with Asperger's syndrome.<ref name="Walker">{{cite web |url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=10479730 |title=Teen hacker has mild autism |date=2007-12-03 |website=NZHerald.co.nz |publisher=NZME. Publishing Limited |access-date=2016-01-11 }}</ref>
==Arrest== {{Main|Akbot}} Walker was arrested under sections 248-252 of New Zealand's Crime Act after international investigations by the [[FBI]] found him to be involved in an attack on the computer network of the [[University of Pennsylvania]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/topic/story.cfm?c_id=199&objectid=10481058&pnum=0 |title=Bot-boy caught in his own net |publisher=New Zealand Herald | date=8 December 2007}}</ref> The attack was orchestrated via a [[botnet]] established by Walker, using servers he exploited and rented, the majority of which were located in [[Malaysia]].<ref name="cw-ateam">{{Cite web | url=http://computerworld.co.nz/news.nsf/scrt/693DE1B864708EABCC25741E0068E114 | title=Owen 'Akill' Walker was part of botnet 'A-team' | publisher=[[Computerworld]] | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080412084041/http://computerworld.co.nz/news.nsf/scrt/693DE1B864708EABCC25741E0068E114 | archivedate=12 April 2008 | df=dmy-all }}</ref>
==Trial== He pleaded guilty to his connection in the crime, was fined for the cost of the damage to the University of Pennsylvania computer and was discharged without conviction, the presiding judge concluded that a conviction would only harm his future.<ref name="NZ_Herald_10521614">{{cite news |url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=10521614 |title=Conviction would harm hacker's future - judge |author=Shenagh Gleeson and Newstalk ZB |date=15 July 2008 |work=[[The New Zealand Herald]] |accessdate=1 November 2011}}</ref>
==Employment== In 2008 he was hired by [[TelstraClear]], the New Zealand subsidiary of Australian telecommunications company Telstra, to work with their security division [[DMZGlobal]]. As a security consultant, he presented seminars and appeared in advertising. TelstraClear spokesman Chris Mirams said it was not the equivalent of hiring a bank robber to advise on bank security.<ref>[http://www.watoday.com.au/national/telstra-offshoot-hires-teen-hacker-akill-20090324-97yn.html?page=-1 Telstra Offshoot Hires Teen Hacker Akill], WAToday [Westarn Australia]</ref>
