{{Infobox person | name = Rina Hasyim | image = <!-- just the filename, without the File: or Image: prefix or enclosing [[brackets]] --> | alt = | caption = | birth_name = Rineke Antoinette Hassim | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1947|04|22}} | birth_place = Makassar, South Sulawesi | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{Death-date and age|Month DD, YYYY|Month DD, YYYY}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | nationality = Indonesian | other_names = | occupation = Actress | awards = {{plain list| *Citra Award for Best Leading Actress *Citra Award for Best Supporting Actress }} | known_for = }} '''Rineke Antoinette Hassim''' (born 22 April 1947), best known by her stage name '''Rina Hasyim''' (also '''Hassim'''), is an Indonesian actress who has won both a [[Citra Award for Best Leading Actress]] and [[Citra Award for Best Supporting Actress]].
==Biography== Hasyim was born Rineke Antoinette Hassim in [[Makassar]], [[South Sulawesi]], on 22 April 1947.{{sfn|filmindonesia.or.id, Rina Hasyim}} Raised strictly by her mother, she began rebelling and gravitated towards music. She was a member of the bands Dara Kusumah and Diskonit while a youth, playing the [[bass guitar|bass]].{{sfn|TIM, Rina Hasyim}}
After completing senior high school, Hasyim moved to the national capital in [[Jakarta]]. Living with her aunt, she began to work at a travel agency. She was soon invited to start modelling by [[Rima Melati]], an actress and model.{{sfn|TIM, Rina Hasyim}} In 1968 she obtained her first film role, a [[bit part]], in Turino Djunaidy's ''Orang-orang Liar'';{{sfn|filmindonesia.or.id, Rina Hasyim}} she obtained the role when her coworker at the travel agency, Mochtar, introduced her to Djunaidy.{{sfn|TIM, Rina Hasyim}}
Hasyim soon married Chris Pattikawa, an employee at the national broadcaster [[TVRI]]; the two had a son the following year.{{sfn|TIM, Rina Hasyim}} In 1970 she appeared in her second role, and first major one, playing a main character's girlfriend in the film ''Si Pitung''.{{sfn|filmindonesia.or.id, Filmografi}} Over the next 25 years Hasyim acted in over a hundred films, sometimes six a year. In 1995 she made ''Gairah & Dosa'', which proved her last feature film for over a decade.{{sfn|filmindonesia.or.id, Filmografi}} She instead focused on television.{{sfn|TIM, Rina Hasyim}} In 2007 Hasyim returned to cinema with ''Pocong 3'', a horror film about [[pocong]]. She has acted in several films since then, though not at as high a rate as during the 1980s.{{sfn|filmindonesia.or.id, Filmografi}}
{{As of|September 2013}}, Widjaja has acted in 113 films.{{sfn|filmindonesia.or.id, Filmografi}} She has been won several acting awards. In 1976 she won the [[Citra Award for Best Leading Actress]] for her role in ''Semalam di Malaysia''. In 1987 her role in ''Akibat Kanker Payudara'' garnered her a Best Supporting Actress at the [[Asia Pacific Film Festival]]. Four years later, she won the [[Citra Award for Best Supporting Actress]] for her role in ''Zig Zag (Anak Jalanan)''; she had previously received five nominations for the award, in 1979, 1981, 1985, 1986, and 1988.{{sfn|filmindonesia.or.id, Penghargaan}}
